  <\definition>
    A Lie Algebra Ł is a <math|K>- Vector Space with an opration [-,-]. Here, [-,-] is a bilinear operation s.t. [<math|x>,<math|x>] = 0 and <math|<around*|[|x,<around*|[|y,z|]>+<around*|[||\<nobracket\>>y,<around*|[|x,z|]>+<around*|[|z,<around*|[|x,y|]>|]>=0|]>,\<forall\>x,y,z\<in\>Ł>

    <\warning*>
      a) [<math|x,x>] = 0 \ \<forall\><math|x>\<in\> Ł

      \<leftrightarrow\> b) <math|<around*|[|x,y|]>+<around*|[|y,x|]>=0 > \<forall\> <math|x,y\<in\>Ł.> \ \ \ \ \ \ <iff> \ \<chi\>(K) \<neq\> 2.

      Reason: <math|<around*|[|x+y,x+y|]>=0> \<leftrightarrow\> <math|<around*|[|x,x|]>+<around*|[|y,y|]>+<around*|[|x,y|]>+<around*|[|y,x|]>=0>.

      \;
    </warning*>

    \;
  </definition>

